			<div class="content" id="post-content-1184285">
									

<p>Well I never saw Talos or the Brass Man in any of the lists of Hephaestus's crafts, but they did say he constructed automatons.<br />
The indesctructable metal was going to be Zeus's Aegis, but it's vague enough to be anything really.<br />
The door-frame, door and lock was supposed to be the ones that were made for Hera, and only she could open the door.<br />
And the statue was supposed to be Pandora, as in one of the lists it said that Hephaestus made her by mixing water and earth, so I reckoned clay was good enough to use.</p>
<p>I'll probably add more to the list, or detail it, if I can think of any other ways for people to fail the crafts without using 'died during engraving' again.</p>

